This paper is about natural language processing and word representations, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses machine learning models and techniques for training these models, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on word similarity and analogy tasks, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
